src.agent_orchestration package

Agent Orchestration core package.

This package provides the foundational data models and interfaces used by the Agent Orchestration Component to coordinate specialized AI agents.

class src.agent_orchestration.Agent(*, agent_id, name=None, coordinator=None, default_timeout_s=10.0)[source]

Bases: AgentProxy

Base Agent abstraction providing: - Standardized async communication helpers (send/receive) - Lifecycle (start/stop/health_check) - Message (de)serialization helpers - Error handling + timeout management - State preservation hooks (export_state/import_state) for recovery

Concrete agents should override process() and optionally health_check() and may override export_state/import_state to persist/restore critical runtime state.

Parameters:

  • agent_id (AgentId)

  • name (str | None)

  • coordinator (MessageCoordinator | None)

  • default_timeout_s (float | None)

class src.agent_orchestration.AgentOrchestrationService(workflow_manager, message_coordinator, agent_registry, therapeutic_validator=None, resource_manager=None, optimization_engine=None, neo4j_manager=None, crisis_intervention_manager=None, emergency_protocol_engine=None, human_oversight_escalation=None, safety_monitoring_dashboard=None)[source]

Bases: object

Main orchestration service providing the primary API for multi-agent coordination.

This service serves as the central coordination layer for TTA’s multi-agent architecture, managing the World Builder Agent (WBA), Input Processor Agent (IPA), and Narrative Generator Agent (NGA) through sophisticated workflow management.

Key Responsibilities: - Route incoming requests to appropriate workflows - Coordinate agent execution sequences - Manage session state and context - Ensure therapeutic safety validation - Handle error recovery and fallback strategies

Parameters:

  • workflow_manager (WorkflowManager)

  • message_coordinator (MessageCoordinator)

  • agent_registry (AgentRegistry)

  • therapeutic_validator (Any | None)

  • resource_manager (Any | None)

  • optimization_engine (Any | None)

  • neo4j_manager (Any | None)

  • crisis_intervention_manager (Any | None)

  • emergency_protocol_engine (Any | None)

  • human_oversight_escalation (Any | None)

  • safety_monitoring_dashboard (Any | None)

Initialize the AgentOrchestrationService.

Parameters:

  • workflow_manager (WorkflowManager) – Manager for workflow registration and execution

  • message_coordinator (MessageCoordinator) – Coordinator for agent message passing

  • agent_registry (AgentRegistry) – Registry for agent discovery and management

  • therapeutic_validator (Any | None) – Optional validator for therapeutic content safety

  • resource_manager (Any | None) – Optional manager for resource allocation and monitoring

  • optimization_engine (Any | None) – Optional engine for performance optimization

class src.agent_orchestration.CircuitBreaker(redis, name, config=None, key_prefix='ao')[source]

Bases: object

Circuit breaker implementation with Redis persistence and configurable behavior.

Follows the standard circuit breaker pattern with three states: - CLOSED: Normal operation, counting failures - OPEN: Failing fast, not executing operations - HALF_OPEN: Testing recovery with limited calls

Redis keys (prefix pfx=ao by default):

  • {pfx}:cb:state:{name} -> JSON state record

  • {pfx}:cb:metrics:{name} -> JSON metrics record

Parameters:

  • name (str)

  • config (CircuitBreakerConfig | None)

  • key_prefix (str)

class src.agent_orchestration.CircuitBreakerRegistry(redis, key_prefix='ao')[source]

Bases: object

Registry for managing multiple circuit breakers with centralized persistence.

Provides circuit breaker lifecycle management, state synchronization, and cleanup operations for expired circuit breakers.

Redis keys (prefix pfx=ao by default):

  • {pfx}:cb:registry -> set of active circuit breaker names

  • {pfx}:cb:state:{name} -> individual circuit breaker state

  • {pfx}:cb:metrics:{name} -> individual circuit breaker metrics

  • {pfx}:cb:cleanup:last -> timestamp of last cleanup operation

Parameters:

key_prefix (str)
